turned out to be Eom Sun-jeong's daughter.

276
00:23:36,164 --> 00:23:39,042
Which helped us confirm
that the car whose license plate

277
00:23:40,085 --> 00:23:42,129
wasn't caught in the dashcam footage

278
00:23:42,212 --> 00:23:44,631
was your car, Ms. Cha.

279
00:23:45,298 --> 00:23:47,050
On February 26,

280
00:23:47,134 --> 00:23:48,635
around 5:00 p.m.,

281
00:23:50,137 --> 00:23:51,555
where were you?

282
00:23:58,436 --> 00:24:00,147
I'll call my lawyer.

283
00:24:16,329 --> 00:24:17,539
What are you doing here?

284
00:24:18,290 --> 00:24:20,125
I'm here because you got in trouble.

285
00:24:20,208 --> 00:24:21,793
What's with the tofu?

286
00:24:22,294 --> 00:24:23,128
So corny.

287
00:24:23,211 --> 00:24:25,130
Just eat it.

288
00:24:25,797 --> 00:24:28,258
You didn't have one
when you were released before, right?

289
00:24:28,341 --> 00:24:30,218
That's why you came here again.

290
00:24:31,219 --> 00:24:33,555
Did you just pull back? I said, eat it.

291
00:24:35,182 --> 00:24:37,142
Fine. I'll eat it.

292
00:24:45,108 --> 00:24:46,776
Is Hwa-jin still in the hospital?

293
00:24:48,361 --> 00:24:49,321
No.

294
00:24:50,155 --> 00:24:51,573
She's occupied with something.

295
00:24:52,199 --> 00:24:53,742
Something? What something?

296
00:24:54,868 --> 00:24:57,162
You're not the only one
who caused trouble.

297
00:24:57,245 --> 00:24:59,539
Hwa-jin got into big trouble. You ask her.

298
00:24:59,623 --> 00:25:01,249
What happened?

299
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:02,792
I don't know.

300
00:25:02,876 --> 00:25:04,669
I said, you ask her yourself.

301
00:25:04,753 --> 00:25:07,297
Aren't you worried about your only friend?

302
00:25:07,964 --> 00:25:10,508
When she got into big trouble
after being discharged?

303
00:25:10,592 --> 00:25:12,010
Hey!

304
00:25:13,094 --> 00:25:17,766
How could I be worrying about her
when my only brother got arrested?

305
00:25:19,809 --> 00:25:22,187
Why are you crying?
You're embarrassing me.

306
00:25:23,563 --> 00:25:27,025
You could've ended up
in jail again, you know.

307
00:25:27,108 --> 00:25:29,194
I told you to stay away from trouble!

308
00:25:29,277 --> 00:25:31,529
I told you to stay away from trouble!

309
00:25:31,613 --> 00:25:33,406
Geez, it hurts.

310
00:25:39,579 --> 00:25:41,289
Ew, gross! Get off of me!

311
00:25:41,373 --> 00:25:43,041
I'm sorry, okay?

312
00:25:44,125 --> 00:25:46,503
Don't worry. I'll be better.

313
00:25:46,586 --> 00:25:48,046
Get off of me.

314
00:25:49,214 --> 00:25:50,257
It hurts.

315
00:25:53,468 --> 00:25:54,844
Eat it.

316
00:25:54,928 --> 00:25:56,930
-I ate it.
-Eat the whole thing.

317
00:26:00,475 --> 00:26:01,685
CHA SU-YEON

318
00:26:01,768 --> 00:26:03,645
I'm serious. Eat the whole thing.

319
00:26:06,273 --> 00:26:08,650
HASEONG MEMORIAL PARK

320
00:26:15,073 --> 00:26:16,241
EOM SUN-JEONG

321
00:26:20,287 --> 00:26:21,538
Was it

322
00:26:22,372 --> 00:26:24,291
really Ms. Cha's doing?

323
00:26:24,874 --> 00:26:27,168
The police are investigating her,

324
00:26:27,252 --> 00:26:28,712
so it'll be on the news soon.

325
00:26:30,130 --> 00:26:31,715
So,

326
00:26:31,798 --> 00:26:33,717
don't do the paternity test.

327
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:36,845
Doing that now will only help Cha Su-yeon.

328
00:26:36,928 --> 00:26:39,431
Why is that helping her?

329
00:26:40,765 --> 00:26:44,227
If she's committed a crime,
she'll go to jail, right?

330
00:26:46,688 --> 00:26:48,315
You're so naive, Hwa-jin.

331
00:26:49,774 --> 00:26:50,984
The president

332
00:26:51,484 --> 00:26:53,153
has the right to grant clemency.

333
00:26:54,654 --> 00:26:57,073
Even if she gets arrested
for a hit-and-run accident,

334
00:26:57,157 --> 00:27:00,535
if Hyun Min-cheol wants to,
he can free her.

335
00:27:00,618 --> 00:27:01,995
And Hwa-jin,

336
00:27:02,704 --> 00:27:04,622
you're the only person who can stop that.

337
00:27:05,248 --> 00:27:06,291
How, though?

338
00:27:07,167 --> 00:27:09,210
With your existence,

339
00:27:10,754 --> 00:27:13,298
he wouldn't dare do it,
even if he's president.

340
00:27:14,299 --> 00:27:17,344
He abandoned your mom,
and his wife killed her.

341
00:27:17,427 --> 00:27:19,429
So how would he dare free her?

342
00:27:19,512 --> 00:27:20,805
I don't understand

343
00:27:21,848 --> 00:27:23,516
what you're saying.

344
00:27:24,726 --> 00:27:26,144
You don't need to.

345
00:27:26,686 --> 00:27:29,230
That's just how things work,

346
00:27:29,314 --> 00:27:31,191
and what matters now is that

347
00:27:31,274 --> 00:27:33,818
you have the power
to make things work that way.

348
00:27:35,945 --> 00:27:39,032
And how would that benefit you?

349
00:27:41,034 --> 00:27:42,577
Remember last time?

350
00:27:43,119 --> 00:27:45,997
After you said you'd give me money
if I did as you said,

351
00:27:47,123 --> 00:27:48,917
you ordered that man to lock me up.

352
00:27:51,878 --> 00:27:52,754
Don't you remember?

353
00:27:55,673 --> 00:27:57,050
Come on.

354
00:27:58,218 --> 00:27:59,719
You can't put it that way.

355
00:28:01,221 --> 00:28:03,264
I didn't lock you up.

356
00:28:04,474 --> 00:28:06,893
I fed you, clothed you,
and put a roof over you.

357
00:28:07,769 --> 00:28:08,770
And what?

358
00:28:10,021 --> 00:28:10,855
Benefit?

359
00:28:10,939 --> 00:28:12,690
I'm getting nothing out of this.

360
00:28:13,483 --> 00:28:17,570
This is all for your mother,
who died unjustly.

361
00:28:24,536 --> 00:28:25,453
Eom Min-jeong.

362
00:28:31,793 --> 00:28:33,294
I'm talking about your mother.

363
00:28:34,838 --> 00:28:38,550
Your mother, who went to jail
after taking the fall for you

364
00:28:38,633 --> 00:28:40,510
and died only a week

365
00:28:40,593 --> 00:28:41,594
after her release.

366
00:28:44,681 --> 00:28:46,099
Mom.

367
00:29:09,497 --> 00:29:10,540
Remember.

368
00:29:11,958 --> 00:29:14,294
You were never here today.

369
00:29:33,813 --> 00:29:38,193
Should I reveal why you abandoned
your name as Eom Min-jeong

370
00:29:39,319 --> 00:29:40,653
and lived as Lee Hwa-jin?

371
00:29:45,950 --> 00:29:48,161
What are you talking about?

372
00:29:48,244 --> 00:29:49,454
Damn it!

373
00:29:57,295 --> 00:29:59,088
Stop putting on a show.

374
00:30:00,465 --> 00:30:02,926
Now that all my cards are on the table,

375
00:30:03,718 --> 00:30:05,386
I can't just sit back and watch.

376
00:30:06,429 --> 00:30:10,225
I noticed you looked great on camera.

377
00:30:11,392 --> 00:30:13,102
Why don't you go on TV again?

378
00:30:13,186 --> 00:30:14,229
Go on TV

379
00:30:14,896 --> 00:30:16,606
and nail Cha Su-yeon's coffin

380
00:30:17,732 --> 00:30:19,567
with your own hands.

381
00:30:20,109 --> 00:30:22,237
So she rots in jail forever.

382
00:30:28,576 --> 00:30:30,787
LATE EOM SUN-JEONG

383
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:36,292
Hello. Please sit here.

384
00:30:41,589 --> 00:30:44,008
What happened on the show that day?

385
00:30:45,009 --> 00:30:46,135
The one with Hwa-jin.

386
00:30:53,685 --> 00:30:55,061
Would you like a drink?

387
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:58,857
When it's so bright out?

388
00:30:58,940 --> 00:31:00,066
Even better.

389
00:31:01,359 --> 00:31:02,944
It's because I'm embarrassed.

390
00:31:04,028 --> 00:31:05,822
What do you mean?

391
00:31:06,823 --> 00:31:07,991
I need a drink.

392
00:31:09,450 --> 00:31:11,411
Excuse me. Can I have a bottle of soju?

393
00:31:11,494 --> 00:31:12,412
Sure.

394
00:31:13,162 --> 00:31:15,373
Drinking in broad daylight. Interesting.

395
00:31:16,499 --> 00:31:18,084
Lawyer Kang asked me

396
00:31:18,626 --> 00:31:19,836
why I became a reporter.

397
00:31:21,462 --> 00:31:22,463
What did you say?

398
00:31:23,965 --> 00:31:25,717
There was definitely a reason,

399
00:31:26,217 --> 00:31:27,427
but I couldn't remember.

400
00:31:28,553 --> 00:31:29,721
Thank you.

401
00:31:30,638 --> 00:31:32,098
Then that happened

402
00:31:32,765 --> 00:31:34,142
on the live show.

403
00:31:36,352 --> 00:31:37,687
Remember my former boss?

404
00:31:38,479 --> 00:31:39,355
The Sewer.

405
00:31:40,982 --> 00:31:42,025
The Sewer?

406
00:31:43,526 --> 00:31:47,447
Because all dirty information went to him,

407
00:31:47,530 --> 00:31:49,991
he was called the Sewer. Gu Jeong-u.

408
00:31:50,742 --> 00:31:53,036
Oh, I remember.

409
00:31:54,704 --> 00:31:56,873
It was a perfect nickname for him.

410
00:31:58,875 --> 00:32:00,919
His first scoop was

411
00:32:01,002 --> 00:32:04,130
Cha Su-yeon being an illegitimate child
when she was seven.

412
00:32:06,090 --> 00:32:07,800
Because of that news,

413
00:32:09,010 --> 00:32:10,678
her mother killed herself.

414
00:32:12,180 --> 00:32:14,724
That was the only useful thing

415
00:32:15,266 --> 00:32:18,353
I learned from him.

416
00:32:20,104 --> 00:32:23,566
That reporters can kill.

417
00:32:34,077 --> 00:32:35,745
That was when I realized

418
00:32:36,329 --> 00:32:38,289
why I became a reporter

419
00:32:38,790 --> 00:32:40,750
and why I couldn't answer him.

420
00:32:45,505 --> 00:32:46,339
I'm sorry.

421
00:32:48,091 --> 00:32:49,926
With the president-elect's divorce

422
00:32:50,009 --> 00:32:52,345
and the situations changing so rapidly,

423
00:32:52,887 --> 00:32:55,306
I was too harsh on you.

424
00:32:56,182 --> 00:32:58,518
They say you take after someone you hate.

425
00:32:58,601 --> 00:33:01,145
I've become like the Sewer myself.

426
00:33:01,771 --> 00:33:03,314
The dark and dirty sewer

427
00:33:03,398 --> 00:33:07,026
where all dirty stuff flows in and out,

428
00:33:07,944 --> 00:33:10,530
using the ratings as an excuse.

429
00:33:16,661 --> 00:33:18,037
You don't have to apologize.

430
00:33:19,205 --> 00:33:20,873
I'm no different from you.

431
00:33:22,709 --> 00:33:25,545
I guess it's true
that you take after someone you hate.

432
00:33:27,296 --> 00:33:29,090
Because that happened to me too.

433
00:33:29,173 --> 00:33:30,508
Who do you mean?

434
00:33:30,591 --> 00:33:31,551
President-elect?

435
00:33:33,511 --> 00:33:35,763
No. I've become like Ms. Cha.

436
00:33:39,559 --> 00:33:42,145
"I won't become like her."

437
00:33:43,563 --> 00:33:46,357
"I could never do things her way."

438
00:33:47,567 --> 00:33:49,652
I used to think that.

439
00:33:50,987 --> 00:33:52,238
Is that why you quit?

440
00:33:58,703 --> 00:34:01,956
I didn't believe it when I heard the news,
but I get it now.

441
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:03,624
You really quit.

442
00:34:04,625 --> 00:34:05,543
How are you sure?

443
00:34:06,919 --> 00:34:10,715
You didn't ask what information I dug up.

444
00:34:11,758 --> 00:34:14,177
Not a question on what I found out
about Eom Sun-jeong

445
00:34:15,094 --> 00:34:18,347
and how I'm going to report the news
and so on.

446
00:34:22,935 --> 00:34:24,353
I guess we won't see

447
00:34:25,396 --> 00:34:26,647
each other again.

448
00:34:31,027 --> 00:34:32,820
We'll meet again soon enough.

449
00:34:35,615 --> 00:34:36,783
When we do,

450
00:34:38,201 --> 00:34:39,702
pretend you don't know me.

451
00:34:45,041 --> 00:34:46,751
TEAM LEADER CHEON

452
00:34:50,588 --> 00:34:52,131
Just leave me alone.

453
00:34:52,215 --> 00:34:54,383
Cha Su-yeon is at Haseong Police Station.

454
00:34:54,467 --> 00:34:57,053
She's being investigated
for Eom's hit-and-run.

455
00:34:58,304 --> 00:35:00,098
Cha Su-yeon and hit-and-run?

456
00:35:01,474 --> 00:35:02,809
Who tipped it off?

457
00:35:02,892 --> 00:35:05,311
That's not important right now.

458
00:35:05,394 --> 00:35:07,688
I confirmed Cha Su-yeon is
at the police station.

459
00:35:08,272 --> 00:35:11,067
Reporter Kim is on the site,
but that's not enough.

460
00:35:11,150 --> 00:35:14,403
You interviewed Hwa-jin
who brought up the hit-and-run accident.

461
00:35:14,487 --> 00:35:17,990
You should report the case yourself
to make it more interesting.

462
00:35:29,502 --> 00:35:31,295
-I got to go.
-Son Min-ju.

463
00:35:33,131 --> 00:35:34,382
My goodness.

464
00:35:35,133 --> 00:35:37,844
Why suddenly call me by my name
being so friendly?

465
00:35:37,927 --> 00:35:39,095
You heard the call.

466
00:35:39,178 --> 00:35:40,304
Is it because of that?

467
00:35:40,388 --> 00:35:42,181
What on earth is happening?

468
00:35:43,266 --> 00:35:44,183
Can I

469
00:35:44,976 --> 00:35:46,602
ask you a favor?

470
00:35:48,646 --> 00:35:50,898
HASEONG POLICE STATION

471
00:35:51,566 --> 00:35:54,110
Gosh, it's been hours.

472
00:35:54,193 --> 00:35:56,571
Where were you at 5:00 p.m.
on February 26?

473
00:35:56,654 --> 00:35:57,738
Just answer that.

474
00:36:02,368 --> 00:36:03,661
This is so frustrating.

475
00:36:04,620 --> 00:36:07,081
Detective, will you give us
some time alone?

476
00:36:08,833 --> 00:36:12,086
I'll talk it out with my client.

477
00:36:16,591 --> 00:36:18,426
You better.

478
00:36:37,236 --> 00:36:40,406
Your schedule is open
to the public anyway.

479
00:36:40,489 --> 00:36:42,325
If you don't cooperate with the police,

480
00:36:43,034 --> 00:36:45,286
it will put you at a disadvantage.

481
00:36:45,369 --> 00:36:47,330
You're here as a witness now,

482
00:36:47,413 --> 00:36:48,706
but if you keep this up,

483
00:36:50,208 --> 00:36:51,918
you could become the suspect.

484
00:36:52,919 --> 00:36:54,337
Cooperate with the police.

485
00:36:58,132 --> 00:36:59,217
Is the camera

486
00:36:59,759 --> 00:37:01,010
turned off?

487
00:37:01,093 --> 00:37:02,511
What?

488
00:37:03,554 --> 00:37:04,513
Yes.

489
00:37:05,348 --> 00:37:07,391
And we're not being voice recorded?

490
00:37:09,685 --> 00:37:11,979
We're not. Why do you suddenly ask--

491
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:14,190
You deceived me, who is your client,

492
00:37:15,399 --> 00:37:17,443
and even stole from me.

493
00:37:21,364 --> 00:37:22,949
I will let it go,

494
00:37:23,491 --> 00:37:24,492
but in return,

495
00:37:28,287 --> 00:37:29,580
I need you

496
00:37:30,665 --> 00:37:32,375
to do something for me.

497
00:37:34,293 --> 00:37:38,839
WORKING WITH LABORERS
KWON HAK-SEON LAW OFFICE

498
00:37:38,923 --> 00:37:40,883
WHY DO INDUSTRIAL ACCIDENTS
REPEAT THEMSELVES?

499
00:37:41,550 --> 00:37:43,803
AUTHOR, KWON HAK-SEON

500
00:37:47,390 --> 00:37:51,560
I'm sorry this is all I have to offer
when you came all the way here.

501
00:37:57,733 --> 00:37:58,985
Lawyer Kwon.

502
00:37:59,068 --> 00:38:01,112
Please chair the Committee.

503
00:38:06,784 --> 00:38:10,121
I remember the day we first met.

504
00:38:10,705 --> 00:38:12,832
You were going to sue

505
00:38:13,374 --> 00:38:16,877
Haseong Petrochemical
for worker's compensation.

506
00:38:20,172 --> 00:38:22,008
You said it was a hopeless fight.

507
00:38:22,633 --> 00:38:24,218
That I could never win it.

508
00:38:24,302 --> 00:38:27,346
I also said
it wasn't your battle to fight.

509
00:38:27,930 --> 00:38:29,640
That you may be like brothers,

510
00:38:29,724 --> 00:38:32,893
but it wasn't a battle you could fight
for someone else.

511
00:38:34,478 --> 00:38:36,397
It wasn't for Tae-hun.

512
00:38:37,148 --> 00:38:38,357
It was for me.

513
00:38:39,317 --> 00:38:42,570
Turning a blind eye
and lying that it was his fault

514
00:38:44,363 --> 00:38:47,074
and not the company's,
just like my coworkers did.

515
00:38:48,909 --> 00:38:50,494
I couldn't bear to see myself

516
00:38:51,704 --> 00:38:54,040
move on with my life
like nothing happened.

517
00:38:55,291 --> 00:38:56,709
You

518
00:38:56,792 --> 00:38:58,294
haven't changed at all.

519
00:39:07,762 --> 00:39:09,430
This place hasn't changed either.

520
00:39:12,516 --> 00:39:14,018
I wasn't going to come to you,

521
00:39:14,977 --> 00:39:17,521
but you're the only one I can trust.

522
00:39:18,147 --> 00:39:20,816
You'll face strong opposition.

523
00:39:21,442 --> 00:39:25,237
I almost lost my lawyer's license
because I blew the whistle on H Group.

524
00:39:25,321 --> 00:39:26,822
If I chair the Special Committee,

525
00:39:26,906 --> 00:39:29,784
people will question its impartiality.

526
00:39:29,867 --> 00:39:32,578
I don't want you to become the judge.

527
00:39:33,871 --> 00:39:36,040
I want you to fight against those

528
00:39:36,832 --> 00:39:38,250
who try to hide the truth.

529
00:39:38,834 --> 00:39:39,877
A sword doesn't

530
00:39:40,878 --> 00:39:42,296
discriminate who it hurts.

531
00:39:48,594 --> 00:39:51,180
I went through the special act.

532
00:39:53,307 --> 00:39:56,268
There's a clause on the investigation
of newly identified cases.

533
00:39:57,144 --> 00:40:02,149
If any evidence were to emerge
that someone was involved in the fire,

534
00:40:02,817 --> 00:40:06,487
the subjects of the investigation
could be expanded.

535
00:40:07,863 --> 00:40:10,699
And your wife

536
00:40:10,783 --> 00:40:12,535
is no exception.

537
00:40:13,119 --> 00:40:14,203
Do you still

538
00:40:14,912 --> 00:40:16,831
want me to take on the position?

539
00:40:29,635 --> 00:40:32,012
Ms. Cha is being investigated
for the hit-and-run.

540
00:40:32,096 --> 00:40:34,682
I found out
as I was checking for an update

541
00:40:34,765 --> 00:40:36,976
on the hit-and-run investigation
as you ordered.

542
00:40:37,059 --> 00:40:39,228
She's called in as a witness.

543
00:40:39,311 --> 00:40:40,396
Let's go to the station.

544
00:40:43,149 --> 00:40:45,317
Reporters have already flocked over there.

545
00:40:46,861 --> 00:40:47,695
So?

