in movies about first love.

681
00:49:16,078 --> 00:49:18,580
You're the perfect first love material.

682
00:49:19,289 --> 00:49:21,583
Are you done nagging? I'm going to bed.

683
00:49:27,047 --> 00:49:28,006
An Gang-myeong.

684
00:49:39,559 --> 00:49:40,602
I'm really going to bed.

685
00:49:41,812 --> 00:49:43,814
Good night, my dear son.

686
00:51:32,547 --> 00:51:34,382
Let's see how much you've grown.

687
00:51:34,966 --> 00:51:37,010
-One span.
-Dad, it's ticklish.

688
00:51:37,093 --> 00:51:38,386
Two spans.

689
00:51:38,470 --> 00:51:40,472
-Stop.
-Three spans.

690
00:51:41,223 --> 00:51:42,432
Four spans?

691
00:51:43,058 --> 00:51:45,435
Five, six spans?

692
00:51:46,061 --> 00:51:47,062
What?

693
00:51:47,604 --> 00:51:49,231
An Gang-myeong, this is cheating.

694
00:51:49,940 --> 00:51:51,525
I told you not to grow so fast.

695
00:51:52,108 --> 00:51:53,902
Didn't I? This is cheating.

696
00:51:53,985 --> 00:51:55,946
-Why are you growing so fast?
-Dad.

697
00:51:56,029 --> 00:51:57,948
-Who said you could?
-Stop. It's ticklish.

698
00:51:58,031 --> 00:51:59,866
-Who said you could?
-It's ticklish.

699
00:52:00,951 --> 00:52:02,035
My goodness.

700
00:52:03,662 --> 00:52:05,038
Don't grow up so fast.

701
00:52:07,123 --> 00:52:09,584
Gosh, my dear son.

702
00:52:56,840 --> 00:52:59,593
It's been hours, damn it.

703
00:53:00,343 --> 00:53:02,345
We might really stay up all night.

704
00:53:03,054 --> 00:53:04,681
She's one tenacious woman.

705
00:53:11,021 --> 00:53:12,147
Lawyer Song.

706
00:53:13,815 --> 00:53:14,900
What brings you here?

707
00:53:14,983 --> 00:53:16,484
Could I have a word with you?

708
00:53:16,985 --> 00:53:18,445
I have something to discuss.

709
00:53:20,614 --> 00:53:22,824
Get out of the way!

710
00:53:22,908 --> 00:53:24,868
Please, get out of the way.

711
00:53:24,951 --> 00:53:26,119
Please, Lawyer Kang.

712
00:53:26,202 --> 00:53:28,872
Please, let me out.

713
00:53:31,249 --> 00:53:33,418
Listen, it was me.

714
00:53:33,501 --> 00:53:35,587
I hit Eom Sun-jeong with a car.

715
00:53:35,670 --> 00:53:37,672
So please let me go.

716
00:53:37,756 --> 00:53:39,299
Ms. Sung.

717
00:53:39,382 --> 00:53:41,927
Ms. Cha repeatedly told me

718
00:53:42,010 --> 00:53:45,597
that you'd lie and say you did it
when you found out where she was.

719
00:53:45,680 --> 00:53:47,515
I'm not lying.

720
00:53:47,599 --> 00:53:49,809
How many times must I say this?

721
00:53:49,893 --> 00:53:51,937
It was me who hit her with a car.

722
00:53:52,020 --> 00:53:53,146
I have to go.

723
00:53:53,229 --> 00:53:54,856
Ms. Cha shouldn't be

724
00:53:54,940 --> 00:53:58,068
at a horrid place like the police station
for even a minute.

725
00:53:58,151 --> 00:53:59,277
Ms. Sung!

726
00:53:59,361 --> 00:54:02,030
Ms. Sung. Ms. Cha told me

727
00:54:03,698 --> 00:54:06,284
to make sure
you didn't go to the police station.

728
00:54:07,118 --> 00:54:09,996
How could I not go?

729
00:54:10,080 --> 00:54:11,706
Because of my old self,

730
00:54:11,790 --> 00:54:14,960
Ms. Cha is going through tough times
in the police station.

731
00:54:15,043 --> 00:54:16,753
How could I not go?

732
00:54:16,836 --> 00:54:20,674
I'm the one that deserves to be punished.
I'm the sinner.

733
00:54:21,716 --> 00:54:22,676
No.

734
00:54:23,802 --> 00:54:26,471
What should I do?

735
00:54:26,554 --> 00:54:27,764
Oh, no.

736
00:54:27,847 --> 00:54:29,891
What do I do?

737
00:54:29,975 --> 00:54:32,852
I need you to do something for me.

738
00:54:32,936 --> 00:54:35,438
When Ms. Sung finds out that I'm here,

739
00:54:35,522 --> 00:54:37,774
she'll definitely want to come over.

740
00:54:37,857 --> 00:54:38,984
So,

741
00:54:39,776 --> 00:54:41,403
stop her from coming here.

742
00:54:50,537 --> 00:54:52,247
It was Ms. Sung

743
00:54:53,665 --> 00:54:56,042
who drove that day, right? It wasn't you.

744
00:54:57,252 --> 00:54:59,004
Is that important?

745
00:54:59,087 --> 00:55:01,756
You're a lawyer
who defends even the guilty, no?

746
00:55:04,676 --> 00:55:08,096
Is that why you've kept your mouth shut
until now?

747
00:55:09,264 --> 00:55:10,390
To take the rap

748
00:55:11,224 --> 00:55:12,559
for Ms. Sung?

749
00:55:12,642 --> 00:55:15,687
You're a lawyer, not a judge.

750
00:55:18,481 --> 00:55:19,607
So,

751
00:55:19,691 --> 00:55:23,236
Ms. Sung is innocent. Do you understand?

752
00:55:24,946 --> 00:55:26,406
Yes, I get what you mean.

753
00:55:27,991 --> 00:55:30,160
But there's a problem.

754
00:55:30,243 --> 00:55:32,662
I am currently your lawyer.

755
00:55:32,746 --> 00:55:34,748
If I'm to defend Ms. Sung,

756
00:55:34,831 --> 00:55:38,418
both you and she need
to sign the Conflict of Interest Waiver.

757
00:55:38,501 --> 00:55:39,502
No.

758
00:55:40,003 --> 00:55:40,879
There's no need.

759
00:55:41,921 --> 00:55:44,674
Lawyer Kang, I am dismissing you.

760
00:55:45,300 --> 00:55:48,386
From now on,
you're no longer my legal representative.

761
00:55:48,970 --> 00:55:51,848
I don't care what happens to me.
Just focus on Ms. Sung.

762
00:55:51,931 --> 00:55:53,183
Then it's good, right?

763
00:55:57,937 --> 00:55:59,022
Ms. Sung.

764
00:56:00,774 --> 00:56:02,901
You said Ms. Cha and I must be like family

765
00:56:03,568 --> 00:56:06,071
since we lived together for a long time.

766
00:56:10,075 --> 00:56:12,327
I didn't give birth to her myself,

767
00:56:13,745 --> 00:56:16,289
but she's more precious
than a daughter to me.

768
00:56:18,374 --> 00:56:22,879
She's the only person I could rely on
for the past 40 years.

769
00:56:31,304 --> 00:56:33,723
And she is now at the police station.

770
00:56:33,807 --> 00:56:36,726
So let me see her at least.

771
00:56:36,810 --> 00:56:38,686
I just want to see her.

772
00:56:39,270 --> 00:56:40,313
I mean,

773
00:56:40,897 --> 00:56:42,565
if I'm innocent,

774
00:56:42,649 --> 00:56:46,486
you can defend me and prove my innocence.

775
00:56:46,569 --> 00:56:50,615
Please. Please let me go see her.

776
00:56:50,698 --> 00:56:53,576
Please, I beg you.

777
00:57:12,470 --> 00:57:14,013
You promised.

778
00:57:14,097 --> 00:57:16,433
We'll just check how she's doing
and come back.

779
00:57:16,516 --> 00:57:18,435
I said I promised.

780
00:57:18,518 --> 00:57:22,480
You can't say you're
the hit-and-run driver like earlier.

781
00:57:23,064 --> 00:57:25,650
You'll get me out anyway.

782
00:57:27,527 --> 00:57:30,363
This isn't the matter of getting you out.

783
00:57:30,947 --> 00:57:32,866
Everyone denies their crimes.

784
00:57:32,949 --> 00:57:34,200
You're the opposite--

785
00:57:34,284 --> 00:57:36,202
How am I not guilty?

786
00:57:37,162 --> 00:57:41,749
I made Ms. Cha suffer for half a day
in that horrendous place.

787
00:57:43,042 --> 00:57:45,503
I hope she hasn't caught a cold
in that cold place.

788
00:57:46,212 --> 00:57:50,300
If she catches a cold around this time,
she'll take long to recover.

789
00:57:54,762 --> 00:57:56,014
My goodness.

790
00:57:56,097 --> 00:57:57,849
How worn out will she become?

791
00:57:58,766 --> 00:58:01,311
She only managed to recover recently.

792
00:58:14,407 --> 00:58:17,494
LIHO EXPRESS

793
00:59:09,921 --> 00:59:12,423
I took care of them as you ordered.

794
00:59:12,507 --> 00:59:14,342
Are you sure it worked this time?

795
00:59:14,926 --> 00:59:17,011
Yes, I'm sure, sir.

796
00:59:33,069 --> 00:59:34,237
I'll do it.

797
00:59:34,320 --> 00:59:35,697
The paternity test.

798
00:59:38,199 --> 00:59:39,534
Ms. Cha is demanding

799
00:59:39,617 --> 00:59:41,578
a paternity test from Lee Hwa-jin.

800
00:59:42,662 --> 00:59:45,832
If Ms. Sung goes to the police station,
Ms. Cha will be released.

801
00:59:45,915 --> 00:59:48,626
She'll do anything for Ms. Cha.

802
01:00:19,574 --> 01:00:22,994
100,000,000 KRW DEPOSITED

